FBIS3-58916 "drweu016__a94035" FBIS-WEU-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 25 January 1994 ANNEX Italy NCC Claims Responsibility for Bomb Attack BR1101113494 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 2244 GMT 10 Jan 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR1101113494 Rome ANSAMAIL Database Language: English Article Type:BFN [Unattributed article: "Bomb at NATO Offices in Rome"] [Text] Rome, 10 Jan (ANSA) -- A caller to the Neapolitan daily IL MATTINO claimed that the Nuclei Communist Combattants (NCC) were responsible for the two-kilogram bomb which exploded outside the NATO Command Defense College offices in Rome shortly after midnight Sunday [9 January] evening. The caller said other sites had been targeted in various Italian cities, including the La Brera railway car plant in Pozzuoli, some ten kilometers outside Naples. Police were investigating the credibility of the claim that the NCC was responsible, a group which has boasted of other attacks in the past.
